The following Python function should return the length of the longest increasing subsequence. It has a bug. Identify and fix it, then provide the corrected code.

```python
def longest_increasing_subsequence(arr):
    if not arr:
        return 0
    dp = [1] * len(arr)
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        for j in range(i):
            if arr[j] < arr[i]:
                dp[i] = dp[j] + 1
    return max(dp)
```
